{{Infobox power station | name = Elean power station | name_official = | image = [[File:Elean power station, Cambridgeshire-Geograph-3366185.jpg|frameless]] | image_caption = Elean power station, Cambridgeshire | location_map = Cambridgeshire | coordinates = {{coord|52.398370|0.131902|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = England | location = [[Sutton, Cambridgeshire]] | status = Operational | construction_began = | commissioned = December 2000 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = EPR Ely Ltd | operator = EPR Ely Ltd | th_fuel_primary = [[Straw]] | th_fuel_secondary = [[Oil seed rape]] | th_fuel_tertiary = ''[[Miscanthus]]'' | ps_units_manu_model = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity= 38 MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | website = http://ely.eprl.co.uk/ | extra = }}
'''Elean power station''' is a [[straw]]-fired [[biomass]] power station in [[Cambridgeshire]], [[England]]. At a capacity of 38 MW, it was the largest straw-fired power plant in the world at the time of its completion.<ref name="ET">{{cite web|url=http://www.engineering-timelines.com/scripts/engineeringItem.asp?id=978 |title=Elean Biomass Power Station |work=Engineering Times |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213020510/http://www.engineering-timelines.com/scripts/engineeringItem.asp?id=978 |archivedate=2014-12-13 |df= }}</ref> The power station was constructed between 1998 and 2000 by FLS Miljo and is operated by EPR Ely Ltd.<ref name="ET"/><ref name="FO">{{cite web|url=http://www.face-online.org.uk/non-food-crops/from-grass-to-grid|title=From Grass to Grid - Farming & Countryside Education|work=face-online.org.uk}}</ref> It generates 270 GWh of electricity from 200,000 tonnes of biomass annually, supplied by Anglian Straw Ltd.<ref name="ET"/> Straw is the major fuel of the plant, but oilseed rape and the [[energy crop]] ''[[Miscanthus]]'' are also used, as well as some natural gas.<ref name="ET"/>
In 2011, the company owning the plant were fined £120,000 after an accident during the unloading of a straw bale lead to the death of a delivery driver.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hse.gov.uk/press/2011/coi-e-0511.htm |title=Power company fined £120,000 after worker is crushed to death |work=hse.gov.uk |date=11 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213032455/http://www.hse.gov.uk/press/2011/coi-e-0511.htm |archivedate=2014-12-13 |df= }}</ref> Later the same year Elean was affected by an arson attack on stacks of straw that were destined to be used at the plant.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-cambridgeshire-16174783|title=Arson attack on 66,000 tonnes of straw in Cambridgeshire|work=BBC News|date=14 December 2011|accessdate=15 June 2015}}</ref>
