{{Icelandic name|Orri}} {{Infobox person | name = Orri Vigfússon | image = Orri Vigfusson, The Green Interview.webm | caption = Orri in conversation with [[Silver Donald Cameron]] about his work. | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date |1942|7|10|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date and age |2017|7|1|1942|7|10|df=y}} | death_place = [[Reykjavik]] | death_cause = lung cancer | monuments = | residence = | nationality = Icelandic | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = entrepreneur and environmentalist | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | influences = | influenced = | home_town = | television = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] }}
'''Orri Vigfússon''' (10 July 1942<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=6zoWAQAAMAAJ&q=Orri+Vigfússon+1942&dq=Orri+Vigfússon+1942&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjwjsC5n-7UAhXFJ5oKHRz8CIwQ6AEIHDAA</ref> – 1 July 2017)<ref>https://www.fishandfly.com/orri-vigfusson/</ref> was an Icelandic entrepreneur and environmentalist. His stated objective was to "restore the abundance of wild salmon that formerly existed on both sides of the North Atlantic".<ref name="goldman"/>
In 2004 [[Time (magazine)|''Time'']] magazine named him a "European Hero".<ref name="Time">[http://www.time.com/time/europe/hero2004/vigfusson.html "Saving the Wild Salmon", Time Europe magazine, 11 October 2004]</ref> He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2007 for his efforts on saving endangered species.<ref name="goldman">Goldman Environmental Prize 2007: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/609 Orri Vigfússon] (Retrieved on 2007-10-25)</ref> <ref name=bbc-april2007>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/6571241.stm "Salmon campaigner lands top award"] &ndash; BBC News (Sunday, 22 April 2007)'' (Retrieved on March 26, 2008)</ref> In 2008, he was elected as a Senior Global Fellow to the [[Social entrepreneurship#Ashoka: Innovators for the Public|Ashoka Fellowship]].<ref name="ashoka">{{Cite web|url = http://ashoka.org/fellow/orri-vigfusson|title = Orri Vigfusson, Ashoka Fellow|date = |accessdate = 2014-10-21|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>
He died on 1 July 2017 in [[Reykjavik]] of [[lung cancer]] at the age of 74.<ref>[http://www.visir.is/g/2017170709867 Orri Vigfússon er látinn] {{is icon}}</ref><ref>[https://www.fishandfly.com/orri-vigfusson/ The world loses the great salmon champion – Orri Vigfússon]</ref>
