'''''Parakneria cameronensis''''' is a [[benthopelagic]] [[species]] of [[tropical fish]]. The species can grow up to  8.3&nbsp;cm, and are commonly found in the [[Congo River]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fishbase.gr/Summary/SpeciesSummary.php?id=11064 |title= Parakneria cameronensis (Boulenger, 1909) |accessdate=2009-11-07 |work=Fish Base }}</ref> The fish has a projectile [[upper jaw]] and subterminal [[mouth]]. The species' [[common name]] is '''Cameroon shellear'''.<ref>{{cite book | last = Many authors | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = The Encyclopedia of Animals | publisher = Welden Owen Inc. | date = 2004 | location = | pages = 481 | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = }}</ref>

